==English==
===Etymology===
From the [[practice]] of the ancients to [[pour]] [[oil]] on the sea [[wave|waves]] to calm them.
===Verb===
'''pour oil on troubled waters'''
# To [[calm]] something or someone who is [[tenacious]] or [[misbehave|misbehaving]].
#: ''I better go pour oil on those troubled waters the [[child|children]] are making over there.''
